I was also interested in doing more venture investing and having had a long working

00:32:17.760 --> 00:32:18.920
relationship with Posit.

00:32:19.239 --> 00:32:22.719
It was kind of the perfect, like the stars aligning, like I can stay involved and

00:32:22.719 --> 00:32:26.680
stay involved in Voltron Data, help Voltron Data succeed, but without being in a

00:32:26.680 --> 00:32:29.479
full-time operator role running the engineering team there.

00:32:29.560 --> 00:32:29.880
Yeah.

00:32:29.880 --> 00:32:30.880
So it was good timing.

00:32:30.880 --> 00:32:35.199
And in the meantime, while working on Voltron Data, our studio rebranded to

00:32:35.199 --> 00:32:40.160
Posit, incorporated Python into its enterprise products, repositioned itself

00:32:40.160 --> 00:32:42.599
to be a polyglot data science company.

00:32:42.880 --> 00:32:47.520
And for me, like I really have been a huge fan of JJ Allaire and Hadley Wickham and

00:32:47.520 --> 00:32:48.719
the leadership at Posit.

00:32:48.719 --> 00:32:53.319
And so to be, take a larger role in the mission of, in the mission of Posit, I

00:32:53.319 --> 00:32:56.400
think it was just the opportunity of a lifetime for me.

00:32:56.400 --> 00:33:01.040
And, and I'm in a position there where I'm able to make important contributions

00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:05.000
to Posit's product offerings to help enhance the experience, not only for

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:08.760
Python data scientists, but for data scientists more generally, regardless of

00:33:08.760 --> 00:33:09.680
programming language.

00:33:10.119 --> 00:33:14.479
But I also have the freedom there to continue working on critical open source

00:33:14.479 --> 00:33:18.239
technologies, work on, if I want to write another book, it's a place where there

00:33:18.239 --> 00:33:21.520
are tons of Posit employees have written books and there's a whole library of

00:33:21.520 --> 00:33:23.040
books written by folks at Posit.

00:33:23.439 --> 00:33:27.040
And so I think for me, it gives me a platform to really, I think, have a lot

00:33:27.040 --> 00:33:28.560
of impact in the data science world.

00:33:28.560 --> 00:33:30.400
So very happy with the transition.

00:33:30.400 --> 00:33:34.760
And as I mentioned, I'm investing in part-time kind of with my new firm, venture

00:33:34.760 --> 00:33:38.839
firm, and yeah, I definitely keep very busy with lots of projects, but I've been

00:33:38.839 --> 00:33:43.079
very fortunate with the connections that I've made and just really looking to do

00:33:43.079 --> 00:33:46.839
what I can to help drive forward the, the open source data science ecosystem.

00:33:46.959 --> 00:33:47.439
Yeah.

00:33:47.599 --> 00:33:52.880
So now you are, is your role more like an individual contributor at Posit?

