So I, yeah, I would say technically I think as a principal architect, I report

00:33:59.160 --> 00:34:02.199
to JJ and so I have, I'm not managing anyone directly.

00:34:02.199 --> 00:34:05.520
So technically that makes me an individual contributor, but I'm doing a

00:34:05.520 --> 00:34:07.280
mixture of, I am writing code.

00:34:07.520 --> 00:34:11.959
It's kind of a mixture of Python and some TypeScript and so working in

00:34:11.959 --> 00:34:13.239
multiple programming languages.

00:34:13.840 --> 00:34:18.919
And I'm also helping with the product roadmaps around like Posit's product

00:34:18.919 --> 00:34:19.360
offerings.

00:34:19.360 --> 00:34:24.479
So Posit Connect, Posit Workbench, Posit Package Manager, sort of Cordo.

00:34:24.679 --> 00:34:27.000
I'm very interested in Cordo as a technology.

00:34:27.040 --> 00:34:31.000
Like I read my third edition of my book, like I migrated to use Cordo and so you

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:32.479
can read it for free on my website.

